Cell.Text: I think we both know... it's time to face my father. | If we don't, he'll keep chasing us for the rest of our lives.
It's... not as shiny as I was expecting. | Still, it's beautiful.
Well, before we spoke to my mother in the Soul Cairn, I would have said we bring the bow to my father. | But after everything with her... I don't think we can trust him.
[S] I've been thinking about this for a long time. | It's... it's not easy. But I don't think we have much of a choice.

Node.Caption: DLC1VQ08SeranaWhatNextDawnguard01: If we do, he'll have to die.

Cell.Text: [S] Have you been paying attention? It's obvious my father's well beyond reason.

Node.Caption: DLC1VQ08SeranaWhatNextDawnguard01b: Maybe we can reason with him.

Cell.Text: [S] There's nowhere to run. And I'm certainly not moving in with my mother, if that's what your implying.

Node.Caption: DLC1VQ08SeranaWhatNextDawnguard01c: Let's run as far from him as we can.

Cell.Text: No. This has to end here and now.

[S] G|If we head back to the castle and kick the front door in, we're going to be knee-deep in his friends. | Let's head back to Isran and let him see what we've got first. I'm betting he'll lend us a sword or two.
[S] I keep thinking that there's got to be another way, but he'll turn on us both the moment he gets the chance.

Node.Caption: DLC1VQ08SeranaWhatNextVampire01a: Then we kill him, before he kills us.

Cell.Text: [S] Have you been paying attention to everything that's happened? He'll betray us the second our backs are turned.

Node.Caption: DLC1VQ08SeranaWhatNextVampire01b: We have the bow, he'll listen to us.

Cell.Text: [S] Are you out of your mind? | The moment you hand over the bow your usefulness ends. He'll kill you and then he'll take my blood for the damn prophecy.

Node.Caption: DLC1VQ08SeranaWhatNextVampire01c: We should honor our agreement with him.

Cell.Text: No. He has to die. We have no choice.
[S] G|Thank you. Somehow I knew you'd understand.
